io.spine.server.storage

Class MessageStorage<I,M extends com.google.protobuf.Message>

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Storage<I,M>, java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AggregateEventStorage, CatchUpStorage, DefaultEventStore, InboxStorage, TenantStorage

    @SPI
public abstract class MessageStorage<I,M extends com.google.protobuf.Message>
extends RecordStorageDelegate<I,M>
    A storage which allows persisting the Messages as storage records.

    The record specification is used to determine the record identifier and the columns.

    To persist the Entity data, see EntityRecordStorage, which uses not only the Entity state, but the Entity lifecycle attributes to prepare the storage record.

    See Also:
    EntityRecordStorage
    Implementation Note:
    This storage delegates all the operations to the underlying RecordStorage, which is configured according to the record specification for the persisted Messages

        public void write(I id,

        Writes the given message under the given identifier.

        The columns are extracted using the record specification.
